Package: roroph
Title: The Philippine Nautical Highway: Roll-on/Roll-Off (RoRo) Connectivity and Transport Data
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person("NJ", "Talingting", 
           email = "ninotalingting77@gmail.com", 
           role = c("aut", "cre"), 
           comment = c(ORCID = "0009-0003-7245-874X"))
Description: Provides the first standardized, machine-readable dataset of the 
    Philippines' Roll-on/Roll-off (RoRo) shipping network, the backbone of 
    the archipelagic nation's inter-island logistics. It digitizes fragmented 
    records from the Maritime Industry Authority (MARINA) and Philippine 
    Ports Authority (PPA) into a unified framework for transport modeling 
    and spatial analysis. The package includes 108 bidirectional provincial 
    links across the Western, Central, and Eastern Nautical Highways, 
    complete with Global Administrative Areas (GADM) standardized naming, 
    geospatial coordinates, and critical transport metrics such as distance 
    (nautical miles), average travel time, vessel frequency, and passenger/cargo 
    capacities. This tool is designed to support high-fidelity research in 
    economic geography, supply chain resilience, and disaster-response 
    logistics within the Philippine context.
